Introduction
------------

perlwm is a window manager written entirely in perl. It requires 
X11::Protocol (available through CPAN http://www.cpan.org/) to run.

Where to get it
---------------

http://perlwm.sourceforge.net/

Usage notes
-----------

Kill your existing window manager (this may require you to log out and
back in in 'failsafe' mode or something similar). Then just start perlwm.

